class DictList(list_type=<class 'list'>)¶

Bases: dict

Wrapper around the common pattern of a dictionary of lists Allows for items of lists to be appended without checking the key exists first x = {} if k not in x.keys():

x[k] = []

x[k] += [v]

Replaced by x = DictList() x[k] += [v]

class dummy_tqdm(*args, **kwargs)¶

Bases: object

Decorate an iterable object, returning an iterator which acts exactly like the original iterable.

Used to replace tqdm when not writing to std.out, prevents ugly output files, should function identically while doing nothing

Can be used as a substitution to make tqdm not a required dependency
